news.title: Jaipur development body’s panel to approve building plans
news.para: Now, zonal offices of the JDA won’t be able to give permissions for construction of buildings. A building plan should get approved only at the building map committee level.

news.title: Asset reconstruction companies vie for ACCIL Corp's Jaipur hotel debt
news.para: Last month, Omkara ARC beat competitor Asset Reconstruction Company of India (Arcil) with a ₹38 crore cash offer to Chennai-based Indian Bank in a Swiss challenge.

news.title: Mumbai: One of last century-old, seafront 'Seven Bungalows' faces demolition
news.para: Once known as Talati Bungalow (named after the Parsi family of Sorabji Talati that once owned it), it is one of the remaining last two of the original Seven Bungalows (Saat Bungla) in Versova.

news.title: NARCL offers Rs 10,000 crore for Jaiprakash Associates' loans
news.para: In the case of JAL, State Bank of India has the largest debt hold at 26%, followed by ICICI Bank at 19% and IDBI Bank at 11%. The company has total principal outstanding debt of ₹17,700 crore as of March 2023.

news.title: Mumbai airport rehabilitation flats 'sold' right after possession
news.para: Last Friday, a function was held at a private banquet hall in Andheri where the local MLA handed over keys of 53 PAP flats. Saki Naka police said some of the recipients illegally sold their flats after receiving the keys outside the banquet hall.

news.title: Villas in Manikonda face bulldozer action for encroaching on Neknampur lake
news.para: Over a dozen multi-crore villas in Manikonda near Neknampur Lake are being demolished due to being constructed illegally in the buffer zone.

news.title: SEBI amends small and medium REITs regulations
news.para: Securities and Exchange Board of India (Real Estate Investment Trusts) (Amendment) Regulations, 2024 applicable to small and medium REITs (SM REITs) will come into force on the date of their publication in the official gazette.

news.title: Bhubaneswar development body to unveil housing project with 700 units
news.para: The housing project is being developed at Subuddhipur on the city outskirts, which will have over 700 dwelling units, the highest ever in any BDA project while the urban forest just adjacent to it, is being developed over a whopping area of 90 acres.

news.title: Stuck RG Luxury Homes project in Greater Noida West now offers possession
news.para: The 18-acre project, RG Luxury Homes, in Greater Noida West was launched in 2010 with an initial deadline of 2014. Facing delays, the construction work was stalled in 2016 due to a fund crisis.

news.title: PM virtually inaugurates light house project in Ranchi
news.para: At a programme in Ranchi, 10 beneficiaries were handed over keys of houses as token distribution, director of Directorate of Municipal Administration Aditya Kumar Anand said.

news.title: Rajasthan government invites bids for 14 sand mining blocks in two districts
news.para: Previously, the department had proposed auctions for 22 blocks in Tonk, Sawai Madhopur, Nagaur, and other districts, but these were recently stayed by the Rajasthan High Court.

news.title: Nilgiris keeps over 4,600 building approval applications pending
news.para: ​While the committee headed by the district collector had received 7154 applications from 2021 to 2023, only 1,727 of them were sanctioned till date.

news.title: Hyderabad: Consumer forum orders Sahiti Infratec to refund Rs 1 crore to two buyers
news.para: The commission bench, comprising its in charge president Meena Ramanathan and judicial member VV Seshu Babu, also directed the real estate firm to pay a compensation of 3 lakh each to the two aggrieved home buyers.

news.title: Bengaluru: Government to relax STP rules for apartment complexes with less than 150 units
news.para: The new guidelines, due for release in a week according to forest minister Eshwar Khandre, may relax the rule of installation of sewage treatment plants (STPs).

news.title: Hyderabad residents grapples with persistent pollution caused by stone quarrying
news.para: The impact on locals has been dire, with residents alleging that these units consistently flout regulations, resulting in health issues such as asthma, lung infection, persistent cough, and migraine.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: 455 slum dwellers get their dream homes
news.para: The housing project has a total of 1,200 dwelling units out of which 960 units have been handed over to the Bhubaneswar Development Authority (BDA).

news.title: US treasury secretary says President's proposed housing tax credits could boost supply
news.para: Yellen said in an interview on MSNBC that Biden's top economic priority was helping Americans deal with higher prices and major living expenses, including the high cost of housing.

news.title: Housing minister says China will improve home sales in 'forceful' way
news.para: China's Minister of Housing and Urban-Rural Development, Ni Hong, pledges to improve home sales in a forceful and orderly way amidst weak demand.

news.title: ED attaches assets worth Rs 367 crore in Bhushan Steel 'bank fraud' case
news.para: A provisional order has been issued under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) to attach the assets that were held "in the name of benamidars/shell entities through dummy directors so as to conceal them and to ensure that they are out of the reach of law enforcement agencies", the ED has said in a statement.

news.title: Six town schemes in Pune may hit poll hurdle unless okayed soon: PMRDA official
news.para: The projects are being planned on the lines of Gujarat model of town planning scheme under which landowners can get back 50% of developed land in the same area.
